  "text": "The Prometheus web UI authentication implementation consists of two main components:\n\n1. **Admin API Access Control** (web/api/v1/api.go): The admin APIs for TSDB management (delete_series, clean_tombstones, and snapshot) are protected by the `enableAdmin` flag in the API struct. Each of the three admin functions checks this flag at the beginning and returns an 'unavailable' error if admin APIs are disabled. The `API` struct is initialized in NewAPI with the enableAdmin parameter passed from the web handler options.\n\n2. **Web Server Authentication Setup** (web/web.go): The Handler's Run method orchestrates the web authentication by delegating to `toolkit_web.ServeMultiple()` from the Prometheus exporter-toolkit. This function handles the actual BasicAuth middleware and TLS client certificate validation based on configuration provided via the web config file.\n\nThe authentication flow:\n- Prometheus main sets up a web config file path via the --web.config.file flag\n- This is passed to Handler.Run() which passes it to toolkit_web.ServeMultiple()\n- The toolkit validates and enforces BasicAuth credentials and TLS client certificates\n- Admin API endpoints register handlers via API.Register() which wraps the admin functions\n- Each admin function checks the enableAdmin flag before executing\n\nKey files and their responsibilities:\n- web/web.go (lines 722-770): Run() method that integrates authentication via toolkit_web.ServeMultiple()\n- web/api/v1/api.go (lines 2026-2102): deleteSeries(), snapshot(), and cleanTombstones() functions that implement admin API access control\n- web/api/v1/api.go (lines 392-484): Register() method that registers all API endpoints including admin APIs\n- web/api/v1/api.go (lines 223-250): API struct containing the enableAdmin field"
}

